.TH "tpm_cr50_i2c_get_burst_and_status" 9 "tpm_cr50_i2c_get_burst_and_status" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tpm_cr50_i2c_get_burst_and_status \- Get burst count and status.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" tpm_cr50_i2c_get_burst_and_status
.BI "(struct tpm_chip *chip "  ","
.BI "u8 mask "  ","
.BI "size_t *burst "  ","
.BI "u32 *status "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "chip" 12
A TPM chip.
.IP "mask" 12
Status mask.
.IP "burst" 12
Return value for burst.
.IP "status" 12
Return value for status.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
cr50 uses bytes 3:2 of status register for burst count and
all 4 bytes must be read.
.SH "RETURN"
- 0:         Success.
- -errno:    A POSIX error code.
